  "prompt": "What are some non-medicinal ways to combat mild to severe depression?",
  "response": "Here are several non-medicinal strategies to help combat depression:\n\n1. Psychological/Therapeutic Approaches\n- Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT)\n- Talk therapy\n- Support groups\n- Counseling\n- Mindfulness meditation\n\n2. Lifestyle Changes\n- Regular exercise\n- Consistent sleep schedule\n- Healthy diet\n- Reducing alcohol/caffeine consumption\n- Limiting social media use\n\n3. Physical Activities\n- Yoga\n- Walking\n- Swimming\n- Strength training\n- Outdoor activities\n\n4. Social Strategies\n- Connecting with friends and family\n- Joining community groups\n- Volunteer work\n- Scheduling regular social interactions\n\n5. Mental Health Practices\n- Journaling\n- Practicing gratitude\n- Mindfulness meditation\n- Setting realistic goals\n- Learning stress management techniques\n\n6. Creative Outlets\n- Art therapy\n- Music\n- Writing\n- Dancing\n- Playing an instrument\n\n7. Natural Approaches\n- Sunlight exposure\n- Spending time in nature\n- Getting sufficient vitamin D\n- Herbal supplements (with professional guidance)\n\nImportant: While these strategies can be helpful, severe depression requires professional medical consultation. These suggestions complement, but do not replace, professional treatment.",
